hello English learners welcome to daily

catalyst let's find out what it means
and how you can use it in your daily
conversation catalyst at times you
experience a change in a situation it
could be in the economy behavior of the
person or technology and you realize
that this change is caused by a driving
force the word catalyst has two meanings
the first one means it is a chemical
substance used to modify and increase
the reaction without it being consumed
in a chemical process the second meaning
is a person thing or an event acting as
a stimulus to cause a change though it's
a scientific term we use it in our daily
English to express a person or a thing
that brings about a change just like a
chemical substance does for example if a
company changes the features of its
product which enhances its quality
further resulting in good sales it means
the change acted as a catalyst for
growth in sales you may also say that
the product enhancement was catalytic
the word catalyst is a noun and
catalysts is its plural form
the word catalytic is an adjective as it
describes a person or a thing that
causes a change to something okay now
that you have understood what catalyst
means let's take a look at some
sentences to see how you can use this
word in your daily conversation example
1 the new amusement park in the city was
the catalyst for growth in tourism
example 2 the new teachers friendly
attitude was the catalyst for making
learning a fun experience for the
students example 3 staying away from his
parents for many years was the catalyst
for John to learn cooking example for
attractive discounts of the store are
always a catalyst for a huge crowd
especially on weekends example 5
increased unemployment and poverty our
catalytic issues as they increase the
anti-social activities in the society
example six the doctor's regular pep
talk was catalytic to keep little Mary
cheerful all the time
example seven the invention of the
mobile phones has been a great catalyst
for faster communication anytime and
anywhere across the globe example eight
personal and professional stress acted
as a negative catalyst for developing
Natasha's addiction to smoking at a
young age example nine the impressive
presentation made by the managing
director aimed at being the catalyst for
motivating the employees to work harder
example 10 frequent delayed departures
are the catalysts for leaving passengers
feeling very restless and dissatisfied
